# MRI Web Viewer Deployment Plan

## Goal
Transform the standalone Python scripts into a web application to "deploy" the MRI viewer. This will allow interactively viewing MRI slices in the browser.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> I am assuming "deploy" implies creating a web interface ([index.html](file:///Users/v.hemanthkumarreddy/.gemini/antigravity/index.html) was open) and running a local web server. I will use **FastAPI** for the backend and **Vanilla JS** for the frontend.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (`mri/server.py`)
- **[NEW]** Create a FastAPI server.
- **Endpoint `/api/data`**: Returns list of available subjects/files.
- **Endpoint `/api/slice/{file_path}/{slice_idx}`**: Returns a specific image slice as PNG/JPEG.
- Use existing [mri_loader.py](file:///Users/v.hemanthkumarreddy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/mri_project/mri_loader.py) logic to load NIfTI files.

### Frontend ([index.html](file:///Users/v.hemanthkumarreddy/.gemini/antigravity/index.html))
- **[NEW]** Interactive UI to:
    - Select MRI file.
    - Slider to scroll through slices (depth).
    - Canvas to display the MRI image.

### Dependencies
- `fastapi`
- `uvicorn`
- `python-multipart`

## Verification Plan
1.  **Start Server**: `uvicorn mri.server:app --reload`
2.  **Browser Test**: Open `http://localhost:8000` via the browser tool to verify the UI loads and slices can be scrolled.
